       <p class="headgreen">Home Branch Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</p>
		<p>Following are some Frequently Asked Questions about our Home Branch service. If you have any other questions, please <%= link_to "e-mail us", new_contact_path %> or call 562-862-8141 during business hours.</p>
        <p class="question">What is Home Branch?</p>
        <p>Home Branch lets you get information about your DFCU account and perform select transactions using any computer with Internet access.</p>
        
        <p class="question">What are Home Branch’s operating hours?</p>
        <p>24 hours a day, seven days a week.</p>
        
        <p class="question">What kind of browser do I need?</p>
        <p>Your browser should support 128-bit encryption. We recommend Internet Explorer 7 or higher or Mozilla Firefox version 3.0 or higher.</p>
        
        <p class="question">How do I access Home Branch?</p>
        <p>Go to <%= link_to "www.downeyfcu.org", root_path %> and click on the Home Branch button. Enter your DFCU account number and Personal Identification Number (PIN).</p>
        
        <p class="question">How do I get a PIN?</p>
        <p>Use your DOTTI PIN. Once you’re in the system, you can select your own PIN.</p>
        
        <p class="question">How much does Home Branch cost?</p>
        <p>There is no fee for using Home Branch.</p>
        
        <p class="question">What kind of transactions can I perform using Home Branch?</p>
        <p>You’ll be able to:
        <ul>
        <li>See current account balances</li>
        <li>Transfer funds from one account to another (for example, from savings to checking)</li>
        <li>Request withdrawals (a check will be mailed to you)</li>
        <li>Transfer funds to another member’s account for which you have authorized access</li>
        <li>Make loan payments</li>
        <li>Get year-to-date dividend and interest paid information</li>
        <li>See when your next loan payment is due</li>
        <li>Access electronic bill payment service - 3rd party fee will be assessed</li>
        <li>View front and back images of cleared checks</li>
        <li>Get the payoff amount for your loans</li>
        </ul>
        </p>
