      <p class="question">When are transactions posted?</p>
      <p>This is a real-time system, so your transactions are effective immediately.</p>
      
      <p class="question">Is Home Branch secure?</p>
      <p>We use the most sophisticated firewalls and encryption software currently available. It would be extremely difficult for anyone to intercept data, and virtually impossible to decode it.</p>
      
      <p class="question">Is there a certain format for entering dollar figures?</p>
      <p>Enter the dollar amount in the following format: 
5.00 (no dollar sign)</p>

<p class="question">I got a "Problem signing on" message. What happened?</p>
<p>Most likely you entered an incorrect account number or PIN.</p>

<p class="question">What does "Connection has expired" mean?</p>
<p>For security purposes, your connection to Home Branch shuts off automatically if there is no activity for 15 minutes. Once you’re in the system, you can adjust the "shutoff" time.</p>

<p class="question">Can I download my account data to my personal financial software?</p>
<p>Yes. You can download info to Quicken&reg; or Microsoft Money&reg;. Simply click on the "Download" button.</p>

<p class="question">How far back does my transaction history go?</p>
<p>You can retrieve account information as far back as the previous 12 months.</p>

<p class="question">If I transfer information to another member’s account, can they see my account information?</p>
<p>No. Only persons with authorized access can retrieve account information.</p>

<p class="question">Are there restrictions on Home Branch transfers as there are on other electronic transactions?</p>
<p>Yes. Federal Regulation D limits transfers from each of your Share Savings Accounts made through Home Branch to a maximum of six per month, while you may make unlimited transfers from checking.</p>

<p class="question">Are there any dollar limits on transfers done through Home Branch?</p>
<p>No. As with DOTTI, transfers on Home Branch are subject only to availability of funds.</p>

<p class="question">Are there any accounts I can’t access through Home Branch?</p>
<p>Yes; Home Equity Loan advances, Certificates, IRAs and Visa cannot be processed online.</p> 
